div.p: Considering files A and B with contents C and D, C & D are going to get squashed together without any separators.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 130px; max-width: 180px; width: 180px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: Compression is fully optional feature that you may have to supply by yourself. You can compress files or entire archive.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 150px; max-width: 180px; width: 180px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: All ASCII characters are allowed in files. Compressing unicode files will require converting these files to ASCII ones and reverse operation after archivement is done.

div.p: Header contains some constant data. Targoviste archive file begins with ASCII codes or "TAR" string.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 170px; max-width: 221px; width: 221px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: After header, decimal (may vary sometimes, official and recommended way is decimal) amount of files in archive is given. Example: "2"

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 220px; max-width: 221px; width: 221.304px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: After amount of files in archive, filename is given (every part of file data is separated with NUL). After filename, there are decimal (as mentioned, may vary) representations of start and end offset.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 170px; max-width: 435px; width: 435.455px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p:
At the moment, Targoviste archive format is easy to adapt changes (thanks for decimal representation of numbers). At the moment, archive size is limited to 4GB. Every archive is solid so you can't just add files.
Extracting and repacking is needed. There are no archive comments, no compression, no SFX, and so on...
No date preservation, no owner preservation, no permission preservation.
